==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squinch
<hw>Squinch</hw> <pr>(skw⟦icr⟧nch)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted
fr. <ets>sconce</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A small arch
thrown across the corner of a square room to support a superimposed
mass, as where an octagonal spire or drum rests upon a square tower; --
called also <altname>sconce</altname>, and
<altname>sconcheon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squinsy</ent>⟦br⟧
